 openly political. Beginning with a discussion of architecture as an illustration of a more general theme of discord and balance, the penultimate lecture probes the inner contradictions of works of art and our reactions to them, while the final piece concerns art and morality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aArts. 0aUt pictura poesis (Aesthetics). 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh  aAcheson Sisters, The (Sargent).  aAdams, Clover (wife of Henry).  aAristotle.  aArrangement in Grey and Black (Whistler).  aBerenson, Bernard.  aBosch, Hieronymus: The Crowning with Thorns.  aChrist.  aCikovsky, Nicolai, Jr.  aClark, Kenneth.  aConstable, John.  aCrowning with Thorns, The (Bosch).  aEidophusikon.  aGrosz, George.  aHolbein, Hans.  aJonson, Ben.  aMilton, John.  aPeale, Raphaelle.  aPlutarch.  aReynolds, Sir Joshua.  aSaint-Gaudens, Augustus.  aSantayana, George.  aSargent, John Singer: The Acheson Sisters.  aSchopenhauer, Arthur.  aSimonides.  aStuart, Gilbert.  aTurner, J.M.W.  aWhistler, J. M.: Arrangement in Grey and Black.  aWindham Sisters, The (Sargent).  aaesthetics.  ade Loutherbourg, Philip James.  adiscord.  a“seely.  a“sense.  a“understanding.  a” selig (Milton).  a” “silly.  a”.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertThe A. W. Mellon Lectures in the Fine Arts eBook Packagez978311129290840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691252827?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691252827423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691252827/original  a978-3-11-129290-8  The A. W. Mellon Lectures in the Fine Arts eBook Package  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles